### VOICE AND TONE RECOMMENDATION

- Recommended Voice: Stylish older sister — knowledgeable, warm, slightly playful
- Tone Characteristics:
  - Encouraging without being over-the-top
  - Editorially confident (makes recommendations, doesn't just list options)
  - Conversational — addresses the reader as "you" throughout
  - British English spelling throughout
  - Enthusiastic about beauty without breathless adjective-stacking
- Language Style: Direct second person ("your nails," "you'll love"), active verbs, short sentences where impact matters. Avoid superlatives stacked together. No em dashes. No banned vocabulary.
- Audience Match: Speaks directly to the overwhelmed, excited teen who has a dress chosen and needs someone to help her narrow it down — not a nail professional, not a product buyer yet.

